http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Thu 6 Oct 2016
Source: Xinhua African News [edited]
http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2016-10/06/c_135735286.htm


Anthrax kills 44 hippos in eastern Zambia: minister
---------------------------------------------------
The Zambian government on Thursday [6 Oct 2016] confirmed an outbreak of anthrax, which has killed 44 hippos in Chama district [Muchinga province] in the country's eastern region.

Minister of Health Chitalu Chilufya said the outbreak of the disease could be due to low water levels, with the 1st case recorded on 22 Sep [2016].

He said in a ministerial statement in parliament that people in the district have since been advised against eating hippo meat because as it was infected with anthrax. "We have dispatched an emergency multisectoral team to Chama and we are sensitizing people in the area not to eat hippo meat," he said.

A mobile laboratory has also been set up in the area and sufficient machines have been provided, he added.

[Byline: Mu Xuequan]

