[The previous reports were not clear as to the 44 cases and we mistakenly assumed these hippo cases were human cases. It appears that there were 22 human cutaneous cases as stated in the last report. Obviously someone has said something to someone and they had 44 hippo carcasses. Obviously a great temptation for those wanting free meat. There should be adequate opportunities to sample the remaining dead hippo. As we have advised before, with carcasses that have been dead for more than 3 days it is best to go straight to the nasal turbinates for tissue to sample. The anthrax spores will remain viable there for at least 3 years in our experience. - Mod.MHJ

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4542091,55934.]
